questions.quote: Oh, hi Elaine. You know I lost all of my 6:30 clients because of you. . . . Yeah, well why did you have to stick your feet in my face? . . . Yes, I have the jacket. Hold on. . . .  Fellas!
Unfortunately, I didn't have a partner. I got gonorrhea from a tractor.
I know his wife. She has some mouth on her. She'll tell everyone in the condo now that you made him give you the pen. They're talking about it right now.
Imagine if I had to see them both on the same day?  Haha! It's like runnin' a double marathon!
What do you think the Nazis were doin'?  That was the heil-five.
Yeah, you should. I certainly remember you. Let me refresh your memory.
I'm trying to buy some of the clothes back.  Hey you wanna come over for dinner tonight? My mother made all this extra Paella.
Not a chance. I'm afraid I'll just have to find someone else to accompany me on my journey. The dark continent is no place for an addict, Elaine.
You know last time you had me throwin' a rye bread up three floors to you, now you want me to go up to the Bronx, take flyers off your car, where does it end?!?
All right, let me ask you something: When do you start to worry about ear hair?
